// src/pages/outdoor/smoker-repair/brands/kamado-joe.astro
// Wave 6a — Kamado Joe brand page (founded 2009 Atlanta GA, Masterbuilt-owned 2018+).
// Classic II/III, Big Joe II/III, Konnected Joe (2023+ — electric auto-ignition + iKamand).
// TWO service trees: traditional kamado (BGE-parallel) + Konnected Joe hybrid (electric).
// $120 OUTDOOR diagnostic universal (per CLAUDE.md §3, smokers = outdoor tier).
// BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410.
// 5 schemas (LocalBusiness + Service + Brand + FAQPage + BreadcrumbList).

import Layout from '../../../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import ServiceHero from '../../../../components/ServiceHero.astro';
import { MAIN_PHONE } from '../../../../data/branches';

const phone = MAIN_PHONE;
const phoneRaw = MAIN_PHONE.replace(/\D/g, '');
const phoneHref = `tel:+1${phoneRaw}`;
const canonical = "https://samedayappliance.repair/outdoor/smoker-repair/brands/kamado-joe/";

const title = "Kamado Joe Smoker Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = `Kamado Joe repair across SoCal. Ceramic + electric service trees. Gasket, dome thermometer, hardware. Premium ceramic kamado. BHGS #A49573. $120 dx.`;

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "What's the difference between Kamado Joe and Big Green Egg from a repair standpoint?",
    a: "On non-Konnected models (Classic II/III, Big Joe II/III), the service tree is parallel: gasket, ceramic, dome thermometer, hardware. The differences are warranty term (Kamado Joe ceramic warranty is 5-10 years depending on component vs BGE lifetime, so out-of-pocket repair on cracked ceramic is more common on Kamado Joe), accessory ecosystem (Kamado Joe ships with more accessories than BGE — divider grates, charcoal basket, deflector plates), and the iKamand option (smart hub controller for non-electric models, accessory). Konnected Joe is its own service tree: it adds electric auto-ignition and digital control, which puts it on a hybrid pellet-style diagnostic."
  },
  {
    q: "My Konnected Joe igniter stopped working at year 2. Is that normal?",
    a: "We're seeing this. Konnected Joe (2023+) introduced electric auto-ignition into the Kamado Joe lineup. Early-production igniter elements have a higher early-failure rate than mature electronic ignition systems. Masterbuilt is processing many of these under parts warranty. Bring us in on the diagnostic, we confirm the failure mode, and if it's the igniter we'll often get the replacement part covered under warranty and bill labor only. Total typical: $120 diagnostic plus $80-120 labor on a warranty-covered igniter. The iKamand smart hub controller has its own service tree separate from the igniter."
  },
  {
    q: "What's iKamand and what fails on it?",
    a: "iKamand is Kamado Joe's smart hub controller, an aftermarket-style accessory that mounts to the bottom damper and uses a small fan to actively control airflow into the firepot for digital temperature management. Available as an accessory on Classic II/III and Big Joe II/III, integrated as standard on Konnected Joe. Common failures: WiFi module connectivity (year 2-4), small fan motor bearing wear (year 3-5), temperature probe drift. Typical repair $200-380 all-in. On the Konnected Joe where iKamand is integrated, the controller is part of the unit's electronic system and the failure tree overlaps with the igniter and damper actuator service."
  },
  {
    q: "How does Kamado Joe ceramic warranty compare to BGE?",
    a: "Shorter. Big Green Egg has lifetime ceramic warranty for registered owners. Kamado Joe currently has 5 years on the dome plus base, 5 years on the fire ring, 3 years on the heat deflector plates and grates. So the warranty navigation play is less powerful on Kamado Joe than on BGE. Out-of-pocket repair on a year-7 cracked Kamado Joe fire ring is more common than on a registered BGE of the same age. We always check the warranty status during diagnostic and route the customer through any active warranty before quoting paid repair."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you stock Kamado Joe parts?",
    a: "Common consumables: gaskets for Classic and Big Joe sizes, replacement dome thermometers, common fastener hardware for hinge and damper. Specialty items (divider grate sets, charcoal basket replacements, fire ring) are dealer-order, 5-7 days standard ship through Masterbuilt's Kamado Joe service network. Konnected Joe igniter elements and iKamand controller modules are dealer-order as well; we coordinate the warranty claim and parts ship simultaneously."
  },
  {
    q: "Can I leave my Kamado Joe outside in the rain?",
    a: "Yes. The ceramic body is weatherproof. Two caveats: keep a Kamado Joe-branded vinyl cover on it to protect the metal hardware (hinge, dampers, draft door, side handle) from rust, and inspect coastal-installed units twice a year for accelerated metal corrosion. The Konnected Joe specifically has electric components that should be kept dry; the iKamand and igniter assembly are weather-resistant but not weather-proof, so cover it."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty?",
    a: "90 days SDAR labor and parts warranty on the work we perform. Kamado Joe component warranties (ceramic for 3-10 years depending on component, plus electronic warranties on Konnected Joe igniter and iKamand) are processed separately through Masterbuilt's Kamado Joe service network. We coordinate active warranty claims and don't charge for parts that the manufacturer is replacing. BHGS #A49573, BBB Accredited, EPA 608 Universal certified #1346255700410."
  }
];

const schemaJsons = [
